# Global Styles

## Source of Truth
agent-os/product/tech-stack.md defines all stack decisions.
agent-os/standards/global.md defines cross-cutting rules.
Never contradict these files.

## Rules
- All colors must use CSS variables — never hardcode hex in components
- Both :root (light) and .dark tokens must always be defined
- No inline styles anywhere in the project
- Tailwind classes reference CSS variables like: bg-[var(--bg-primary)]

## Font Variables
--font-display: Space Grotesk
--font-body: Inter
Apply both to html element via next/font

## CSS Variable Tokens

### Light Mode (:root)
--bg-primary: #ffffff
--bg-secondary: #f5f5f5
--bg-card: #efefef
--text-primary: #0a0a0a
--text-secondary: #444444
--text-muted: #888888
--custom-border: #e0e0e0
--lime: #0a0a0a

### Dark Mode (.dark)
--bg-primary: #0a0a0a
--bg-secondary: #111111
--bg-card: #1a1a1a
--text-primary: #f5f5f5
--text-secondary: #a3a3a3
--text-muted: #555555
--custom-border: #222222
--lime: #f5f5f5

## Base Rules
- html: scroll-behavior smooth
- body: antialiased, bg-[var(--bg-primary)], text-[var(--text-primary)]
- Custom scrollbar: 6px, matches theme
- ::selection: inverted colors
